  "analysis_summary": "Document analyzes 2026 Brazilian presidential election with key candidates: Lula (incumbent, PT), Bolsonaro allies (Flavio), center-right challengers (Caiado, Zema), and emerging figures (Renan Santos, Ciro Gomes). Key institutions include TSE (electoral authority) and STF (Supreme Court). Polling data from Datafolha, Quaest shows Lula at 39%, Bolsonaro at 35%. Important dynamics: economic paradox (good macro indicators vs poor perception), 'SUS do Transporte' policy proposal, legislative coalition bargaining, anistia bill for January 8th protesters, and rising youth support for libertarian candidates. Media ecosystem includes major TV networks and polling institutes conducting up to 28 presidential debates.",
